## 1. Course description 🟢

This course introduces students to the full-stack web development lifecycle using Java-based technologies. Students learn front-end design with HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and ReactJS, followed by server-side programming using JDBC, Servlets, JSP, and Spring Boot. The course emphasizes building database-driven web applications and integrating front-end and back-end components into a complete mini-project.

---

## 2. Course content (units & weightage) 🟢

| Unit | Syllabus | Weightage |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Introduction to Full Stack Web Development, MVC architectures, web servers, HTML5, CSS, responsive design basics | 25 Marks |
| 2 | HTML layout features, media queries, box model, JavaScript fundamentals, DOM, Regular Expressions, exception handling, event handling | 25 Marks |
| 3 | JDBC, JDBC drivers, database connectivity, Servlets, GET/POST, session handling, cookies, JSP, JSTL, form-based JSP integration | 25 Marks |
| 4 | ReactJS components, state, props, forms, hooks, Spring Boot overview, MVC vs Boot flow, dependency injection and autowire | 25 Marks |

---

## 3. 🔵 Dual-level scope of each unit (KEYSTONE)

| Unit | Awareness level — every student must reach (floor) | Advanced level — required to exceed 8 CGPA (ceiling) |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Identify types of web architectures, create semantic HTML pages, and style forms using CSS | Build production-oriented web pages with reusable layout patterns and responsive design refinements |
| 2 | Create JavaScript functions, manipulate DOM elements, validate form inputs, and handle basic events/errors | Design modular validation flows, reusable event handlers, and robust client-side form logic |
| 3 | Connect Java applications to a database using JDBC, create basic Servlets/JSP pages, and manage sessions/cookies | Build secure, session-aware database applications with cleaner controller logic and JSP/JSTL integration |
| 4 | Create React components with state/props and explain Spring Boot architecture and dependency injection | Develop a small React + Spring Boot full-stack application with component composition, service layer design, and autowired connectivity |

